<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}+{9}{y}={32}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{x}+{4}{y}={15}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1},{4}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -1. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{1}}{{4}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{1}}}{{4}}{\left({4}{x}+{9}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{1}}}{{4}}{\left({32}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({1}\right)}{x}+-{2.25}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}+{4}{y}={15}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1.75}{y}={7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{7}}{{1.75}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={4}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}+{9}{\left({4}\right)}={32}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}+{\left({36}\right)}={32}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}={32}-{\left({36}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}=-{4}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{4}}{{4}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{1}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1},{4}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

